1. Parsing:
- "-?", help/usage
- "-c", --count=NUMBER of packets
- "--ttl=N" (N time to live) (nb of hops)
- "-v", --verbose
- "-W", --linger => nb of seconds to wait for response
- "-p", --pattern=PATTERN
- "-q", --quiet
- "8.8.8.8" (dest) ou "ww"

2. Initialise ICMP header and initialise buffer (modify with pattern if needed)
- don't forget to create checksum() to check packet integrity

3. Open a socket and initialise socket options (timeout and ttl)

4. Send packet
